<br>
&quot;Why should I leave a useful channel like /auc or /taxi because someone decides to spout antisemetic, racist or other offensive nonsense.&quot;<br>
-  No one is asking nor will make you leave these channels.  If someone undesirable enters, once again, silence them with /ignore.  It is not within our rights to silence another, despite their offensiveness, in these settings.  The best you can do is take care of yourself;  /ignore them.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think private/password channels are a bad idea. Thats all.&quot;<br>
- Personally, I think they're great.  If you want to talk with a group of friends who are not all guilded or who you want to be 'private' with, use a 'private' channel.  What more can you ask than that?  A place all to yourself and your friends where only people you trust to be mature or whatever you choose to be will be admitted, through your telling them the password.<br>
